title: Mark Levin Audio Rewind - 2/4/20
description:
On Tuesday's Mark Levin Show, it looks like the Democrat Party interfered in another election — their own, in Iowa. The did a better job voting in Iraq. CNN is reporting that turnout in Iowa has been similar to 2016 and that enthusiasm is up by 7% in favor of Republicans. Then, President Trump has announced that he will be awarding the Presidential Medal of Freedom to radio legend Rush Limbaugh. Limbaugh will also be a guest at this evening's State of the Union address. Later, this partisan impeachment is not what the framers had in mind, these ideologies are alien to Locke and Montesquieu — it’s a struggle between liberty and the iron fist.
